# LLM Backend (pick one):

# Option 1: Groq (FREE, fastest — recommended)
# Get a free key at console.groq.com
# GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_your_key_here

# Option 2: Ollama (FREE, local, no internet needed)
# Install: curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh
# Then: ollama pull llama3.1:8b
# USE_OLLAMA=1
# OLLAMA_HOST=http://localhost:11434
# OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.1:8b

# Option 3: Claude CLI (default — uses your Claude Code subscription)
# No config needed, just have claude installed
